fillIncArray

public static int[] fillIncArray(int len,
                                 int startVal,
                                 int inc)
Returns an array of given length whose indices are filled with incrementing integers. The integers begin in cell 0 from a given start value and increment by a given value.

Parameters:
len - the length of the array to be filled.
startVal - the value to start counting from
inc - the value to increment by

printArrayI

public static void printArrayI(int[] arr)
Prints the indices of the given array and the array itself. The indices are printed on a first line and the array is printed below it. Tabs are used to line up the indices with their appropriate elements.

Parameters:
the - array to be printed

toDouble

public static double[] toDouble(int[] arr)
Typecasts an array of integers to an array of doubles. Each element of the original array is typecasted indiviually and placed in the same location in a new array of type double.

Parameters:
